(748, 'Fidel and the Russian Ambassador, Aleksander Alekseev, had worked on it together through the night of October 26/27 1962', 'NNP CC DT JJ NNP NNP NNP VBD VBN IN PRP RB IN DT NN IN NNP CD CD', '2,9,7,14', NULL),
(749, 'Two days after Fidel''s letter was sent to Khrushchev, on October 29, Alekseev sent a cable to Khrushchev in an effort to clarify what he, Alekseev, thought might be some ambiguity in Fidel''s own letter', 'CD NNS IN NNP NN VBD VBN TO NNP IN NNP CD NNP VBD DT NN TO NNP IN DT NN TO VB WP PRP NNP VBD MD VB DT NN IN NNP POS NN', '2,14,19,22', NULL),
(750, 'Alekseev''s account provides a rare window on a leader struggling, in the fog of a deep and confusing crisis, with the catastrophic options he is facing, as Cuba prepares for Armageddon', 'NNP NN VBZ DT JJ NN IN DT NN VBG IN DT NN IN DT JJ CC JJ NN IN DT JJ NNS PRP VBZ VBG IN NNP VBZ IN NNP', '3,7,11,6', NULL),
